{SOUTH has a great 1NT hand - 17 points and 4-3-3-3 shape.

NORTH has 16 points; he figures it is possible that SOUTH can make a slam, but only 
if she has a 17 point opener. So he bids 4NT, expecting SOUTH to bid 6NT if she has 17 points 
but to pass if she has fewer.

He figured right - SOUTH had 17 points so she bid 6NT.}

